library(p8105.datasets)

set.seed(1)
data("nyc_airbnb")

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2) %>% 
  rename(boro = neighbourhood_group,
         neighborhood = neighbourhood) %>% 
  filter(boro != "Staten Island") %>% 
  select(price, stars, boro, neighborhood, room_type)
fit = lm(price ~ stars + boro, data = nyc_airbnb)

Be careful with factors

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(boro = fct_infreq(boro),
         room_type = fct_infreq(room_type))

fit2 = lm(price ~ stars + boro, data = nyc_airbnb)
nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(boro = fct_relevel(boro, "Brooklyn"),    # "Brooklyn is used to compared"
         room_type = fct_infreq(room_type))

fit3 = lm(price ~ stars + boro, data = nyc_airbnb)

Rather than compared to Bronx, they compared to Manhatten

Nesting and fitting

nest_lm_res =
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(boro) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  mutate(models = map(data, ~lm(price ~ stars + room_type, data = .x)),
         models = map(models, broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(-data) %>% 
  unnest()

Lets go nuts

manhattan_airbnb =
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(boro == "Manhattan")

manhattan_nest_lm_res =
  manhattan_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(neighborhood) %>% 
  nest() %>% 
  mutate(models = map(data, ~lm(price ~ stars + room_type, data = .x)),
         models = map(models, broom::tidy)) %>% 
  select(-data) %>% 
  unnest()

View some results

manhattan_nest_lm_res %>% 
  filter(str_detect(term, "room_type")) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighborhood, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~term) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 80, hjust = 1))

Binary outcome

baltimore_df = 
  read_csv("data/homicide-data.csv") %>% 
  filter(city == "Baltimore") %>% 
  mutate(resolved = as.numeric(disposition == "Closed by arrest"),
         victim_age = as.numeric(victim_age),
         victim_race = fct_relevel(victim_race, "White")) %>% 
  select(resolved, victim_age, victim_race, victim_sex)
